The sample rate command, sr, reports or changes the sample rate of
the audio.  Type sr and press enter to report it.  Press sr, a space,
and the desired value to change it.  Valid rates are between 5000
and 50000 samples per second, or more accurately, frames per second.
If the current rate and the desired rate are a multiple of two, Edway
does the conversion itself.  If not, the helper program sox is invoked
to do the conversion.

